Nooku Symlinker
---------------

Make symlinks for Joomla extensions. This very useful to separate your Joomla 
installation from your extension project, but connect them using symlinks. That 
way you don't have to copy changes back and forth.

Works on *nix, OSX, Vista+


Installation:

Put the files somewhere in your operating system's include path. Install PEAR Command Line using this command:
pear install --alldeps Console_CommandLine


Usage:

  symlinker <SOURCE> <TARGET>

Options:
  -h, --help     show this help message and exit
  -v, --version  show the program version and exit

Arguments:
  SOURCE  The source dir (usually from an IDE workspace containing the extension)
  TARGET  the target dir (usually where a Joomla installation resides)

